parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or suddenly accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission produces a loud clanking or grinding noise
the vehicle suddenly accelerates or decelerates
the engine RPM surges or drops
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the vehicle may lurch or jerk while shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or harsh shifting can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or suddenly accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle lurches or jerks while shifting
the engine RPM surges or drops
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or suddenly accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transfer case produces a loud noise
the vehicle suddenly accelerates or decelerates
the engine RPM surges or drops
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle stalling and loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire sidewall failure can lead to sudden blowouts, loss of control, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
The combination of heavy vehicle weight and inadequate tire and rim design can lead to tire blowouts, rim damage, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially when hitting potholes or small obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire manufacturing defects can lead to premature tire failure, blowouts, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Gas Pedal Design Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal and gas pedal can cause accidental acceleration, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The tip of the foot hits the accelerator while trying to brake
causing the vehicle to accelerate instead of stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, and loss of control.
symptoms: and the vehicle jerks or decreases in speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Stalling and cruise control failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and the check engine warning light illuminates.
